---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { getAppBySlug, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = getAppBySlug('wardrobe-studio')
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="Terms for using Wardrobe Studio, including accounts, local wardrobe data, Pro purchases, and Apple platform services."
>
  <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
  <p>
    By downloading, accessing, or using Wardrobe Studio, you agree to these Terms of Use. If you do not
    agree, do not use the app. These terms are intended to work alongside Apple&apos;s App Store terms
    and any mandatory consumer protection laws that apply to you.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital
    Product Studio brand.
  </p>
  <p>
    These Terms are in addition to, and do not replace, Apple&apos;s standard terms that apply to apps
    distributed through the App Store.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Description of the App</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio helps you organize clothing, save garment photos and details, build outfits, track
    wears, plan trips, maintain a wishlist, receive optional reminders, view widgets, and unlock Pro
    features where available.
  </p>

  <h2>3. User Responsibilities</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for using Wardrobe Studio lawfully, keeping your device and account access secure,
    entering accurate information, keeping your backups safe, and making sure you have the right to
    upload, store, share, or export any photos, product links, notes, or other content you add to
    the app.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Accounts</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may support guest mode and account-based features. If you create an account, you are
    responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your credentials and for activity under your
    account. Account authentication may be provided through Firebase or another backend service used
    by Wardrobe Studio.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use Sign in with Apple, your account access is subject to Apple&apos;s sign-in flow and your
    Apple ID settings.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Account Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    If Wardrobe Studio allows account creation, the app will provide a way to request or initiate account
    deletion from within the app, subject to verification and legal retention requirements. Deleting
    the app may remove local app data from your device, but it may not automatically delete any
    account or provider-side records.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may offer Pro features through monthly, yearly, or lifetime purchases. All purchases
    and subscriptions are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store. Subscription management,
    cancellations, and refund requests are handled through the user&apos;s Apple ID account and
    Apple&apos;s App Store settings.
  </p>
  <p>
    The specific Pro features, price, billing period, renewal terms, and any trial terms are shown
    in the app before purchase. Pro features may include expanded wardrobe limits, advanced outfit
    planning, wishlist tracking, trip packing tools, widgets, backups, or other premium features
    shown in the app before purchase.
  </p>
  <p>
    A lifetime purchase, where offered, grants access to the specified Pro features for the lifetime
    of the app as made available by the developer, subject to app availability, platform
    limitations, and these Terms.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Cancellation and Refunds</h2>
  <p>
    You can manage or cancel Apple-billed subscriptions through your Apple ID subscription settings.
    Refund requests are handled by Apple according to Apple&apos;s App Store policies and applicable
    consumer law. Wardrobe Studio cannot directly cancel Apple-billed subscriptions or issue App Store
    refunds outside Apple&apos;s process.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Your Content and Backups</h2>
  <p>
    You keep ownership of the wardrobe content you add to the app, such as garment photos, item
    details, outfits, wear logs, wishlist links, and backup files. You grant Wardrobe Studio the limited
    permission needed to store, display, process, and export that content so the app can provide its
    features.
  </p>
  <p>
    Manual backup files can contain your wardrobe data and photos. You are responsible for where you
    save, share, or transmit those files.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Recommendations, Weather, and External Content</h2>
  <p>
    Outfit suggestions, weather-aware recommendations, stats, style summaries, and trip plans are
    provided for convenience and general informational use. They may be incomplete, unavailable, or
    inaccurate. Product pages, retailer websites, product images, and external services accessed
    through links or the share extension are controlled by third parties.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio recommendations are provided for personal organization and convenience only. They are
    not professional fashion, safety, weather emergency, travel, or financial advice.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wishlist links and target prices are provided for personal organization only. Wardrobe Studio is not
    responsible for product availability, price accuracy, shipping, returns, or purchases made on
    third-party retailer websites.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Intellectual Property</h2>
  <p>
    The app, its content, design, branding, and related materials are protected by intellectual
    property laws. You may not copy, modify, distribute, or reverse engineer the app except where
    permitted by applicable law.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Availability and Changes</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio may be updated, changed, suspended, or discontinued at any time. Features may vary by
    platform, device, operating system version, App Store availability, network availability, and
    account or purchase status.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, the app is provided as is and without warranties of any
    kind. We are not liable for indirect, incidental, consequential, or special damages arising from
    use of the app, including loss of data, loss of wardrobe records, lost backup files, purchase
    issues handled by Apple, or reliance on recommendations.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about these Terms of Use, contact <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}
      >{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
